name: Bakso Super Premium
address: Jl. Raya Sibang Kaja No.78, Sibang Kaja, Kec. Abiansemal, Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80352, Indonesia
review 1:
Pro:
- Price is affordable. Range between 10k-30k
- Their Boba is ok - price around 15K.

Con:
- Not as advertise in the picture. In their pics and menu, the presentation seemed we will get a bowl of bakso (couples of bakso, pangsit & egg) but in reality we only got 4 small balso.  when we ordered Bakso Keju at 20K - We got 4 small Bakso Keju. Well it's 20K anyway. But please don't put that in your menu.
- Bakso beranak seemed so small than Bakso beranak supposed to be. It was just regular bakso tenis.
- Not as premium as it supposed to taste. Well  the price is not premium either.
- Pangsit - it was not pangsit like you see in the pic. It was krupuk.

Overall, on top of 10-30K, you will need add kerupuk (not pangsit) & drink. You will end up paying the same when you buy Bakso Subur, Bakso Supra Dinasty, Bakso Buka Baju - which taste better.. sorry but this is just my honest review
review 2: The location is quite strategic on the side of a big road with a striking red name sign which is very easy to find.  The template is spacious and the parking lot is quite large.  The staff is friendly and swift to handle orders.  For flavors from 1 - 10, I gave a score of 6, too much MSG for me.  Cleanliness must also be improved
review 3: We love it! Great broth. My daughter loves the bakso keju. The mie ayam is top notch. Great local food at a great price!
review 4: Many varieties of meat balls, and also noodles. Yumylicious with affordable prices..
review 5: Seen a lot of local people coming here, so I wonder what's special. The Bakso Lobster or lobster chicken(meat)ball are affordable, though I can't really taste the lobster because the soup has strong flavor. So for me the taste are not that special, so I guess people come here for the affordable price. Thus the chicken noodle are nice, the chicken is tasty.
